Oct 10 2009 	One of THE places to stay in a fantastic city	This was our first trip to San Francisco and part of a 3 centre trip to the West Coast. The MO provided us with one of the most memorable introductions to the city, we arrived by BART from the airport and emerged into the downtown area during a busy Friday lunchtime and it appeared like most cities.On arriving at hotel and being taken up to our room on the 41st floor we got our first amazing view of a the city from the glass walkway near the lifts. This continued in our room a Bridge to Bridge room giving us a 180 degree view of the bay and the city. We never closed our curtains whilst there so we didn't miss a minute of the view. We were also greeted by champagne and strawberries arranged by a friend as this was our 'honeymoon' after our civil partnership and also chocolates from the manager, all in the room on arrival shortly followed by the tea and almond biscuits. The hotel provided us with an excellent base to explore the city, even if the area around the hotel was very quiet over the weekend, but thanks to advise by the hotel we discovered the farmers market at the ferry building on the Saturday one of many highlights of our trip. As MO fans we were not disappointed and our stay strengthened our preference for the MO brand.	
